freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: 3 painful apthous-like ulcers on the hard palate for seven days, they finally have resolved today. Feeling fatigued for past 3-4 days.  Seems like my post nasal drip is worse this week, maybe my allergies. Normal temp, but early morning sweats.
Some vague mild abdominal symptoms, dull pain, felt bloated.  Inappetance, couple of episodes of nausea for about an hour in the morning, no vomiting

Vague abdominal pain on and off last week, hot flashes. Felt hot & drenched w/ sweat this morning, temp was normal. Very tired today, took my walk, but feel exhausted. Brief period of nausea this morning, not hungry until afternoon.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Mild intermittent cough today. I had mild jabbing pain in area of abdomen just under the rib cage yesterday evening, vague discomfort mild abdomen which are gone this afternoon
My upper arms and shoulders are sore and feel tired, as if I had been working out and had muscle strain.  My injection site is in the left deltoid and only mildly painful to direct pressure.
No fever but intermittently hot, better this afternoon
Sharp stomach pains this morning, mild, cleared up before I ate breakfast
